==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*filu'', from Indo-European ''*pelu-, pel-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[filo]], [[filu]]'' (Dutch ''[[veel]]''), Old High German ''[[filu]]'' (German ''[[viel]]''), Old Norse ''fjǫl-'' (in compounds), Gothic [[𐍆𐌹𐌻𐌿]].  The Indo-Euorpean root is also the source of Greek ''[[πολύς]]'', Latin ''[[plus#Latin|plus]]'', Old Irish ''[[il#Old Irish|il]]'' (Welsh ''[[lliaws]]'').

